<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1542,2037]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1542,1568]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A pair of processes on male abdominal sternite VI long (&gt; 
<quantity box="[967,1076,1542,1569]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
), slightly divergent and curved inward (
<figureCitation box="[244,334,1579,1605]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 9G</figureCitation>
). Phallal sheath apically looking like arrowhead in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1155,1579,1605]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 11I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1542,2037]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,531,1614,1640]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Supplementary description.</emphasis>
Supracervical setae 6–9 per side, nearly straight, as long as inner occipital setae (
<figureCitation box="[160,247,1651,1677]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Characters 1‒4 on the head of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A‒D) and C. cristata de Meijere (E‒H). A, E, Caudal view; B, F, dorsal view; C, G, frontal view; D, H, right eye (frontal view). Abbreviations: ar, arista; a rc orb s, anterior reclinate orbital seta; i ocp s, inner occipital setae; pc orb s, proclinate orbital seta; spc s, supracervical setae. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766408/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Cibarial, medial sensilla 2–3 per side; posterior sensillum 1 per side (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1140,1651,1677]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,798,822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[151,1435,181,774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Characters 5 and 6 on the cibarium (dorsal view) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. cristata de Meijere (B) and C. sarawakana sp. nov. (C). Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensillum; s c, sensilla campaniformia. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766410/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Supralateral seta outside prementum 4–5 per side (
<figureCitation box="[457,564,1687,1713]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1350,1374]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,344,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-90@29.[151,1435,344,1326]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 19. Colocasiomyia cristata de Meijere (♂ and ♀ from Bogor, West Java, Indonesia). A, Antenna; B, dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view; yellow arrowheads indicating supralateral setae outside prementum); C, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female abdominal sternites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766444/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Anterior dorsocentral setae just beside transverse suture (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1354,1686,1713]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Male abdominal sternite III as wide as long; IV wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[836,940,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1350,1374]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,344,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-90@29.[151,1435,344,1326]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 19. Colocasiomyia cristata de Meijere (♂ and ♀ from Bogor, West Java, Indonesia). A, Antenna; B, dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view; yellow arrowheads indicating supralateral setae outside prementum); C, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female abdominal sternites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766444/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 19C</figureCitation>
). Female abdominal sternites IV–VI longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[279,385,1759,1785]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1350,1374]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,344,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-90@29.[151,1435,344,1326]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 19. Colocasiomyia cristata de Meijere (♂ and ♀ from Bogor, West Java, Indonesia). A, Antenna; B, dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view; yellow arrowheads indicating supralateral setae outside prementum); C, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female abdominal sternites (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766444/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 19D</figureCitation>
). Epandrium pubescent except for anterior margin and anteroventral elongation, roundish on posteroventral margin, with approximately 2 setae on dorsal portion and 23–24 setae thicker than cercal setae on ventral portion of each side (
<figureCitation box="[487,593,1831,1857]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). Cercus pubescent on dorsal half but not on anterior margin and ventral portion, extended below, slightly constricted ventrosubapically in lateral view, with approximately 42 setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). Phallapodeme less sclerotized thin plate, nearly perpendicular to phallal axis (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1246,1903,1929]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 11H</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct not pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[278,409,1939,1965]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,762,786]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,182,734]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1435,181,737]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Characters 48‒51 on the female terminalia of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, hypoproct in ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, hypoproct in ventral view). Abbreviations: epiprct, epiproct; hyprct, hypoproct; ov, oviscapt; t-VIII, tergite VIII. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766426/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 12C,D</figureCitation>
). Oviscapt gently sinuate, as long as phallus (apodeme + sheath), apically round, with patch of pubescence on subdistal portion and 20–21 ovisensilla only on distal portion occupying less than 1/2 length of oviscapt (
<figureCitation box="[260,363,2011,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,762,786]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,182,734]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1435,181,737]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Characters 48‒51 on the female terminalia of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, hypoproct in ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, hypoproct in ventral view). Abbreviations: epiprct, epiproct; hyprct, hypoproct; ov, oviscapt; t-VIII, tergite VIII. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766426/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
